## Rules

1. Do not break the public API without an explicit major version bump.
2. Do not add new top-level dependencies without discussing in an issue first.
3. Run `{{ check_command }}` before every commit — it must pass with zero errors.
4. Do not commit generated files (dist/, build artifacts, *.tsbuildinfo).
5. Do not disable linters or strict mode for individual files.
6. Every new function needs a unit test.
7. Every bug fix needs a regression test.
8. Inspect staged files before every commit.
9. Do not include `Co-authored-by` trailers.
10. Do not use destructive git commands unless explicitly requested.

